activities.message:
Thanks, folks! 
@badger, I am fine with going public in sync with the pending next release.
By the way, as a side question, in future if I encounter issue in the code base that I suspect it may be a vulnerability but need to discuss further with the developer such as yourself before submitting it as a report, how should I proceed? The reason I ask is because curl enforces a Signal Requirement.

Simple fix:

~~~diff
diff --git a/lib/vssh/libssh2.c b/lib/vssh/libssh2.c
index f1154dc47..08271deac 100644
--- a/lib/vssh/libssh2.c
+++ b/lib/vssh/libssh2.c
@@ -726,15 +726,14 @@ static CURLcode ssh_check_fingerprint(struct Curl_easy *data)
     /* Before we authenticate we check the hostkey's sha256 fingerprint
      * against a known fingerprint, if available.
      */
     if((pub_pos != b64_pos) ||
        strncmp(fingerprint_b64, pubkey_sha256, pub_pos)) {
-      free(fingerprint_b64);
-
       failf(data,
             "Denied establishing ssh session: mismatch sha256 fingerprint. "
             "Remote %s is not equal to %s", fingerprint_b64, pubkey_sha256);
+      free(fingerprint_b64);
       state(data, SSH_SESSION_FREE);
       sshc->actualcode = CURLE_PEER_FAILED_VERIFICATION;
       return sshc->actualcode;
     }
